== Grilled Chicken ==

Preheat your grill to medium-high. Pop the @British Chicken Breasts{2} on a
foil lined #baking tray{} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Zest the
@Lemon{1} using the fine side of your #grater{}. Massage a splash of @oil{},
a pinch of lemon zest, salt and a grind of black pepper into your chicken and
keep to one side.

Wash your hands and get on with the rest of your prep. Cut the @Echalion
Shallot{1} in half through the root, peel and then slice into thin half moon
shapes. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{} if you
have one). Remove the core from the @Red Pepper{1} and cut into slices
1cm thick.

Pop a #saucepan{} on medium heat and add a splash of oil. Add your shallot
and cook for ~{5%minutes}. Once soft add your pepper and cook for ~{5%minutes}
more. Then add your garlic and @Saffron{1} and cook for ~{1%minute} more.
Add the @Water{500%ml}, bring to the boil and then add the @Freekeh{100%g}.
Season with a generous pinch of salt and reduce the heat to medium-low. Cook
your freekeh for ~{15%minutes}.

With the freekeh cooking away, pop your chicken under your grill and cook for
~{20%minutes}. Turn after ~{10%minutes} to make sure both sides colour evenly.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

== Zahtar Dressing ==

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @Flat Leaf Parsley{1%handful}(roughly chopped) and
@Mint{1%handful}(roughly chopped). Cut the @Red Chilli{1/2} in half lengthways,
scrape out the seeds and then thinly slice the chilli widthways.

Pop the @Za'atar{1} spice into a #small bowl{} and add a squeeze of lemon
juice, a quarter of your parsley, all your mint and a splash of oil per person.
Mix well and add a pinch of salt and as much chilli as you dare. This is your
zahtar dressing.

== To Serve ==

When your freekeh is cooked, drain off any excess liquid through a #sieve{}.
Return your freekeh to the pan off the heat mix in your remaining parsley and a
good splash of lemon juice. Taste and add more salt and black pepper if
necessary.

Slice each chicken breast into six slices and serve on top of a generous
portion of freekeh. Finish the dish with a drizzle of your zahtar dressing.
Enjoy!